  "title": "Admin Assistant -Relevant working experience within the logistics industry",
  "description": "<p>Junior Administrative Assistant</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Support daily office operations by performing administrative and clerical tasks, managing data entry and documents, handling communications, and assisting various departments to ensure smooth workflow.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Enter data accurately into designated systems to maintain up-to-date records</li><li>Organize and file documents systematically to support efficient document retrieval</li><li>Answer phone calls professionally and assist with managing email correspondence to facilitate communication</li><li>Support daily office operations by coordinating tasks and resources as needed</li><li>Assist other departments with administrative tasks to promote teamwork and operational efficiency</li><li>Use basic Microsoft Office tools (Word, Excel, Email) to complete assigned tasks effectively</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Email) to perform administrative duties</li><li>Minimum GCE ‘O’ Level or equivalent qualification</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Willingness to learn new skills and take responsibility for assigned tasks</li><li>Good communication skills to interact effectively with colleagues and external contacts</li><li>Well-organized approach to managing workload and office tasks</li><li>Positive working attitude to contribute to a collaborative work environment</li></ul><p>Working Hours:</p><ul><li>5-day work week</li></ul>",
